From: "Kirill A. Shutemov" <kirill.shutemov@linux.intel.com>
Date: Thu, 14 Nov 2013 14:31:24 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] alpha: handle pgtable_page_ctor() fail

References: Automatic NUMA Balancing (fate#315482)
Patch-mainline: v3.13-rc1
Git-commit: 3fd681b68cd34eacb106b25fcb10bb202a3232c5

Signed-off-by: Kirill A. Shutemov <kirill.shutemov@linux.intel.com>
Cc: Richard Henderson <rth@twiddle.net>
Cc: Ivan Kokshaysky <ink@jurassic.park.msu.ru>
Cc: Matt Turner <mattst88@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Linus Torvalds <torvalds@linux-foundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Mel Gorman <mgorman@suse.de>
---
 arch/alpha/include/asm/pgalloc.h | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/alpha/include/asm/pgalloc.h b/arch/alpha/include/asm/pgalloc.h
index bc2a0da..aab14a0 100644
--- a/arch/alpha/include/asm/pgalloc.h
+++ b/arch/alpha/include/asm/pgalloc.h
@@ -72,7 +72,10 @@ pte_alloc_one(struct mm_struct *mm, unsigned long address)
 	if (!pte)
 		return NULL;
 	page = virt_to_page(pte);
-	pgtable_page_ctor(page);
+	if (!pgtable_page_ctor(page)) {
+		__free_page(page);
+		return NULL;
+	}
 	return page;
 }
 
